fields.description:
When registering a kernel and ramdisk as a non-admin, non-eucalyptus (i.e. cloud admin account) user, the error returned is very odd. Its understood that this type of user does not have the ability to register kernels and ramdisks, but the error message should be consistent with what non-eucalyptus account, admin users see.  (Refer to EUCA-5721 for additional information).

{code}
## bundle, upload, and register kernel ##
# euca-bundle-image -i images/appscale/appscale-1.6.8-euca/vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2 --kernel true
Checking image
Compressing image
Encrypting image
Splitting image...
Part: vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2.part.00
# euca-upload-bundle -b kernel-upload-test-v2 -m /tmp/vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
Checking bucket: kernel-upload-test-v2
Creating bucket: kernel-upload-test-v2
Uploading manifest file
Uploading part: vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2.part.00
Uploaded image as kernel-upload-test-v2/vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
# euca-register -a x86_64 kernel-upload-test-v2/vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
RegisterImageType: Failed to read manifest file: kernel-upload-test-v2/vmlinuz-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml

### bundle, upload, register ramdisk ##
# euca-bundle-image -i images/appscale/appscale-1.6.8-euca/initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2 --ramdisk true
Checking image
Compressing image
Encrypting image
Splitting image...
Part: initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.part.00
Generating manifest /tmp/initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
# euca-upload-bundle -b ramdisk-upload-test-v2 -m /tmp/initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
Checking bucket: ramdisk-upload-test-v2
Creating bucket: ramdisk-upload-test-v2
Uploading manifest file
Uploading part: initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.part.00
Uploaded image as ramdisk-upload-test-v2/initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
# euca-register -a x86_64 ramdisk-upload-test-v2/initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xmlRegisterImageType: Failed to read manifest file: ramdisk-upload-test-v2/initrd.img-2.6.32-350-ec2.manifest.xml
{code}
